Derivatives in R

2022-08-02

ex_A <- expression(x ^ 2)

my_derivative <- deriv(ex_A, "x")

x <- 3

eval(my_derivative)
## [1] 9
## attr(,"gradient")
##      x
## [1,] 6
ex_B <- expression((2 * ((3 * a) + 2) ^ 4) - 5)

my_derivativeb <- deriv(ex_B, "a")

a <- 1.2

eval(my_derivativeb)
## [1] 1961.899
## attr(,"gradient")
##             a
## [1,] 4214.784
ex_C <- expression((-4 * t)/((t^2) + 1)^3)

my_derivativec <- deriv(ex_C, "t")

t <- 0

eval(my_derivativec)
## [1] 0
## attr(,"gradient")
##       t
## [1,] -4
